WEBVTT

00:01.243 --> 00:03.318
And the squeak, squeak, squeak
of Dan's flossing

00:03.320 --> 00:06.230
with his pinky in the air...
Ugh.

00:06.232 --> 00:08.340
...makes me want him
to hit an artery

00:08.342 --> 00:12.160
and just float away
on a pool of his own blood...
Mm-hmm.

00:12.162 --> 00:14.329
...the floss dangling
from his teeth.

00:14.331 --> 00:16.331
Mm. When Diana
would drink water,

00:16.333 --> 00:18.242
which was the only thing that
she actually liked in life...

00:18.244 --> 00:21.261
[ Chuckles ] Oh.
...she would drink and then
she would smack her lips --

00:21.263 --> 00:22.521
[ Smacks lips ]
No.

00:22.523 --> 00:24.431
And then go, "Oh, wow,
that's refreshing,"

00:24.433 --> 00:26.250
as if it's news
that water's refreshing.

00:26.252 --> 00:27.934
I wanted to rip her lips
off her face.

00:27.936 --> 00:29.102
Yes.

00:29.104 --> 00:30.512
I mean, I do miss it,
but...

00:30.514 --> 00:32.865
I'll tell you what -- what
really makes me quite violent

00:32.867 --> 00:34.424
is when Henry plays
the guitar,

00:34.426 --> 00:35.850
he makes --
I don't even know what.

00:35.852 --> 00:37.277
It's like
the most earnest face.

00:37.279 --> 00:38.871
It's like --
It's like...mmm.

00:38.873 --> 00:40.764
I don't even know what it is.
Oh, don't do that.
Don't do that.

00:40.766 --> 00:43.191
But what I want to do is I want
to punch him in that face

00:43.193 --> 00:44.451
and then I want
to punch him again

00:44.453 --> 00:46.194
and then I want to
just flick him

00:46.196 --> 00:47.862
as, like,
the final insult.

00:47.864 --> 00:49.623
Hey, guys.
Hey, boo.

00:49.625 --> 00:53.385
I am gonna go make
some of my famous<i> gazpacho.</i>

00:53.387 --> 00:54.035
Ooh.

00:54.037 --> 00:54.869
Yeah.

00:55.964 --> 00:59.391
I don't know how you stay
married to him.
I wanna rip my ears
off my head.

00:59.393 --> 01:00.726
Why?

01:01.878 --> 01:03.395
Oh.

01:03.397 --> 01:05.138
Well, not everyone
likes a cold soup.

01:05.140 --> 01:07.624
I get it.
It's not for everyone.

01:07.626 --> 01:10.718
♪♪

01:10.720 --> 01:11.962
♪ Hey! ♪

01:11.964 --> 01:15.574
♪♪

01:15.576 --> 01:18.635
[ Mumbling ]

01:18.637 --> 01:20.395
[ Groans ]

01:21.398 --> 01:23.974
Ben:<i> Of course, I know</i>
<i> Sasha's upset with me,</i>

01:23.976 --> 01:25.567
<i> but it's the right decision.</i>

01:25.569 --> 01:28.570
<i> It's really a bummer that</i>
<i> I ruined my shot with Sasha,</i>

01:28.572 --> 01:32.999
<i> but I do believe deep down that</i>
<i> Priscilla and I could...</i>

01:33.001 --> 01:43.009
♪♪

01:43.011 --> 01:53.019
♪♪

01:53.021 --> 02:03.029
♪♪

02:03.031 --> 02:12.965
♪♪

02:12.967 --> 02:14.191
[ Farts ]

02:14.193 --> 02:17.427
[ Mumbles ]

02:19.974 --> 02:22.048
[ Gags ]

02:22.050 --> 02:24.125
[ Rapid footsteps approaching ]

02:24.127 --> 02:26.036
Mom, Evan's trying
to cut my hair!

02:26.038 --> 02:27.204
'Cause it looks
like crap!

02:27.206 --> 02:28.630
It does not
look like crap.

02:28.632 --> 02:30.390
But seriously, Nora,
run a brush through it.

02:30.392 --> 02:32.542
You guys, you have to go
make the bus.

02:32.544 --> 02:34.394
I can't take you
to school today.

02:34.396 --> 02:35.970
I'm late
for an appointment.

02:35.972 --> 02:37.156
Mom, can I have cash?

02:37.158 --> 02:39.307
Backpacks on. Now, go!
What for?

02:39.309 --> 02:40.993
Drugs.
Crack, specifically.

02:40.995 --> 02:42.310
I really hope that's not true,
Andrea.

02:42.312 --> 02:43.887
Is $5 enough?
Thank you.

02:43.889 --> 02:45.647
Mm!

02:45.649 --> 02:47.332
Wait, no, that's mine!

02:48.410 --> 02:49.484
[ Sighs ]

02:49.486 --> 02:51.837
Come on, guys.
We gotta get the bus.

02:51.839 --> 02:56.233
♪♪

02:56.235 --> 02:58.159
Jodie.
Whoa!

02:58.161 --> 03:00.070
Dan, what are you
doing home?

03:00.072 --> 03:03.432
I tried to go to work,
but I don't feel well.

03:05.244 --> 03:06.426
I think
I'm gonna throw up.

03:06.428 --> 03:09.354
Oh.
Is there a trash can
you prefer I use?

03:09.356 --> 03:11.081
Is -- Is the toilet
not an option?

03:11.083 --> 03:14.267
No, I mean to put
beside the bed.

03:14.269 --> 03:16.195
Or I could just lie
with my head

03:16.197 --> 03:17.696
pressed against
the cold floor.

03:17.698 --> 03:19.364
You know what?
I think it's dealer's choice.

03:19.366 --> 03:20.866
Just please don't use
a wicker trash can
from the kids' room.

03:20.868 --> 03:21.849
I'm so sorry.
I've got to go.

03:21.851 --> 03:23.093
Jodie!

03:23.095 --> 03:25.320
Do you think you could stay?
I'm dizzy.

03:26.432 --> 03:29.599
And what if I pass out
and hit my head?

03:29.601 --> 03:32.461
I wouldn't want you or the kids
to find me like that.

03:34.273 --> 03:35.288
♪♪

03:35.441 --> 03:37.774
I don't want you to die
like that, either.

03:37.776 --> 03:39.867
♪♪

03:39.869 --> 03:42.387
It's coming.
Yeah.

03:42.389 --> 03:45.540
Oh, w-would you get my computer,
please?

03:45.542 --> 03:46.708
Mm.

03:46.710 --> 03:50.187
♪♪

03:53.049 --> 03:54.066
[<i> Ringing</i> ]

03:54.068 --> 03:57.027
[ Cellphone ringing ]

03:57.905 --> 04:00.130
Hey, you.
Jodie:<i> Hey, you.</i>

04:00.132 --> 04:01.982
<i> Hi.</i>
Uh-oh.

04:01.984 --> 04:03.891
I know that "hi."
What's wrong?

04:03.893 --> 04:05.244
I'm so sorry to do this
last minute,

04:05.246 --> 04:07.729
but I'm not gonna be able
to make it to our session today.

04:07.731 --> 04:09.063
My kid is sick.

04:09.065 --> 04:10.415
Take it off my series,
though.

04:10.417 --> 04:11.992
No, no, no.
Don't even worry about it, no.

04:11.994 --> 04:13.477
<i> I know you got a lot</i>
<i> on your plate.</i>

04:13.479 --> 04:15.996
Half greens, quarter protein,
and a quarter carbs --

04:15.998 --> 04:17.589
complex, not simple.
Not simple.

04:17.591 --> 04:18.815
[ Chuckles ]

04:18.817 --> 04:19.907
Dan: I'm gonna blow again!

04:19.909 --> 04:21.001
Need another trash can!

04:21.003 --> 04:22.486
I'll be there
in just a minute!

04:22.488 --> 04:24.096
[ Whispering ]
But I'm running in place.

04:24.098 --> 04:25.489
I'll lose the last pound
from home.

04:25.491 --> 04:27.173
How about
those jumping jack twists

04:27.175 --> 04:28.267
that I'm trademarking
for my program?

04:28.269 --> 04:30.102
<i> They will blast</i>
<i> the calories.</i>

04:30.104 --> 04:31.995
Here we go.
And jack and twist!

04:31.997 --> 04:33.013
And jack and twist!

04:33.015 --> 04:34.848
<i> Jack! Twist!</i>
<i> Jack! Twist!</i>

04:34.850 --> 04:36.016
Too late!

04:36.018 --> 04:37.501
Ugh.
I'll call you back.

04:37.503 --> 04:38.685
<i> High knees!</i>

04:38.687 --> 04:40.428
<i> Keep those knees high,</i>
<i> and I'm gonna send you</i>

04:40.430 --> 04:42.114
<i> a home workout video</i>
<i> that I recorded.</i>

04:42.116 --> 04:44.007
Little glitch --
it plays upside down,

04:44.009 --> 04:45.675
but otherwise,
it's cool.

04:45.677 --> 04:49.270
♪♪

04:49.272 --> 04:50.438
Oh, uh...

04:50.440 --> 04:52.791
No, I-I'm Luke's mother.
I'm not trespassing.

04:52.793 --> 04:53.959
No, I know,
Mrs. Lakier.

04:53.961 --> 04:55.352
Security
recognizes you now.

04:55.354 --> 04:56.870
Quick thing.
Man...

04:56.872 --> 04:58.112
Hey.

04:58.114 --> 04:59.706
Uh, today at recess,
the kids were playing

04:59.708 --> 05:02.876
in their cars on the playground,
and Macy cut Luke off,

05:02.878 --> 05:04.528
drove in front of him,
bumped into him,

05:04.530 --> 05:07.197
and he called her
a "bleeping bleep bleep."

05:07.199 --> 05:10.291
Well, I mean,
is she a bleeping bleep bleep?

05:10.293 --> 05:12.536
Let's just say she's not
a good driver

05:12.538 --> 05:16.056
and too old to pronounce
the word animal "aminal,"

05:16.058 --> 05:17.390
but regardless,

05:17.392 --> 05:19.376
we try and encourage
our students to be kind

05:19.378 --> 05:21.320
and fill each others' buckets
with positivity.

05:21.322 --> 05:23.304
Shoot. Did Luke need a bucket
for school?

05:23.306 --> 05:25.398
No,
it's a metaphorical bucket.

05:25.400 --> 05:28.051
Okay, well,
that's way cheaper.

05:28.053 --> 05:29.995
Yeah. So when this sort of thing
happens,

05:29.997 --> 05:31.479
we usually find
that it's because

05:31.481 --> 05:34.833
the child is parroting
something they hear at home.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.409
Okay, so you mean like
a babysitter?

05:36.411 --> 05:39.504
Oh, no, no, no, no.
We<i> love</i> Gloria here.

05:39.506 --> 05:40.413
Please say hi.

05:40.415 --> 05:42.156
This is
a more recent change.

05:42.158 --> 05:44.401
Puberty.
Nope, that's a ways off.

05:44.403 --> 05:46.327
Well, I developed very early,
okay?

05:46.329 --> 05:47.420
I mean,
it was great at first.

05:47.422 --> 05:49.422
It was kind of fun
and exciting,

05:49.424 --> 05:52.926
and then changing in gym class
got a little...you know.

05:52.928 --> 05:54.427
I'm sure it was.

05:54.429 --> 05:56.613
So, uh,
not to assign blame...
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

05:56.615 --> 06:00.192
...but it's probably a parent
Luke's parroting.

06:00.194 --> 06:03.436
Mm. Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm.

06:03.438 --> 06:04.196
[Bleep]

06:04.198 --> 06:05.697
[Bleep]
[Bleep]

06:05.699 --> 06:07.090
[Bleep] [Bleep]

06:07.092 --> 06:08.700
[ Tires squealing,
car horns honking ]

06:08.702 --> 06:10.202
[Bleep] [Bleep]

06:11.947 --> 06:13.430
Okay, I'm gonna go,

06:13.432 --> 06:15.265
'cause these kids
aren't gonna wipe themselves.

06:15.267 --> 06:17.267
Okay, hey, I will --
I'll talk to Luke's dad

06:17.269 --> 06:18.359
about being
a better role model.

06:18.361 --> 06:20.587
He's a real loose cannon,
okay?

06:23.032 --> 06:24.699
Wait,
why did I come here?

06:24.701 --> 06:26.126
Oh, God. Luke.

06:26.128 --> 06:28.461
[ Laughs ]
You get it.

06:28.463 --> 06:30.130
♪♪

06:30.132 --> 06:31.539
[ Door closes ]

06:31.541 --> 06:32.465
Hey, Bri.

06:32.467 --> 06:36.043
I got you some groceries
at Fields.

06:36.045 --> 06:37.062
Hi.
Hey.

06:37.064 --> 06:38.471
These are
all about to expire,

06:38.473 --> 06:41.048
so if I were you,
I'd get on it.
Oh, wow.

06:41.050 --> 06:42.901
Thank you.
You are spoiling us.

06:42.903 --> 06:43.977
Where's Lila?

06:43.979 --> 06:46.053
Napping, I hope.

06:46.055 --> 06:47.147
That cheap baby monitor
I got

06:47.149 --> 06:49.390
only picks up
the neighbor's Ring cam.

06:49.392 --> 06:51.134
I think the wife's
having an affair.

06:51.136 --> 06:53.412
The pest guy
stays there way too long.

06:53.414 --> 06:54.413
What a mess.

06:54.564 --> 06:55.972
You know, I've been meaning
to clean out

06:55.974 --> 06:58.324
this closet for awhile.

06:58.326 --> 07:00.902
God,
Coleen was such a slob.

07:00.904 --> 07:03.404
Oh, my God.

07:03.406 --> 07:05.815
This is the scarf!
What scarf?

07:05.817 --> 07:07.150
Uh,<i> the</i> scarf.

07:07.152 --> 07:08.260
I don't know what
you're talking about.

07:08.262 --> 07:10.077
The one!
The one with the chickens on it!

07:10.079 --> 07:12.264
She said that you tried
to tie her up with this.

07:12.266 --> 07:16.159
Okay, it's roosters,
and, no, I did not.

07:16.161 --> 07:17.661
Unless she said
it was great.

07:17.663 --> 07:19.162
[ Laughs ]

07:19.164 --> 07:20.997
I don't think that "great"
was the word.

07:20.999 --> 07:23.090
I think it was...

07:23.092 --> 07:26.019
"awkward, embarrassing,"
oh, and "sad."

07:26.021 --> 07:27.504
But it was
a good story.

07:27.506 --> 07:29.096
That she wasn't supposed
to tell anyone.

07:29.098 --> 07:31.432
She didn't.
Just me, Jodie, and Amy.

07:31.434 --> 07:33.359
Oh. For the record,
I did a great job.

07:33.361 --> 07:35.120
The problem
was her wrists.

07:35.122 --> 07:38.198
For such a thin woman,
she had very thick wrists.

07:38.200 --> 07:40.441
It's why she always
wore men's watches.

07:40.443 --> 07:42.535
You know, Brian, not everybody's
great at bondage.

07:42.537 --> 07:45.538
Okay, Coleen was
a very unreliable narrator.

07:45.540 --> 07:48.875
I will show you exactly
how good I did.

07:48.877 --> 07:51.528
Oh.
Come on. Get in there.

07:51.530 --> 07:53.029
Be my guest.

07:53.031 --> 07:54.789
The first thing I can tell you
you did wrong

07:54.791 --> 07:56.199
without seeing anything

07:56.201 --> 07:57.976
is that you used a scarf
with chickens on it.

07:57.978 --> 07:59.627
Again, roosters,

07:59.629 --> 08:02.129
and it was the only scarf
that she'd let us ruin.

08:02.131 --> 08:03.356
It was a gift
from my mom,

08:03.358 --> 08:06.059
which probably added
a creepy layer to things.

08:06.061 --> 08:08.061
Mm-hmm.
Might be why
it didn't work out.

08:08.063 --> 08:09.562
And done.

08:09.564 --> 08:12.899
See, I don't think
it was her fat wrists,

08:12.901 --> 08:14.475
may they rest in peace.

08:14.477 --> 08:15.552
I think it was you.

08:15.554 --> 08:17.070
Why don't you
have a seat...
Okay.

08:17.072 --> 08:18.905
...and I will show you
how it's actually done.

08:18.907 --> 08:20.481
You remember my ex,
Diana.

08:20.483 --> 08:21.816
Mm-hmm.
She was a freak.

08:21.818 --> 08:24.093
Couldn't tie her legs together.
You know what I mean?

08:24.095 --> 08:25.987
So, uh -- Oh.

08:25.989 --> 08:28.081
What else did Coleen
tell you about me?

08:28.083 --> 08:30.825
Um, that you cry
at rom-coms,

08:30.827 --> 08:32.919
uh, you love
the Dave Matthews Band,

08:32.921 --> 08:34.254
and that you sit
when you pee.

08:34.256 --> 08:36.181
Every man does when
no one's around.

08:36.183 --> 08:38.499
You have a blankie
named Bolly.

08:38.501 --> 08:41.594
You barricade the doors at night
in case of an intruder.

08:41.596 --> 08:43.413
Because zombies.

08:43.415 --> 08:44.264
Yeah.

08:44.266 --> 08:45.932
Amy: Alright,
heads up, Luke.

08:45.934 --> 08:48.268
Glass incoming.

08:48.270 --> 08:51.863
Watch where you're going,
you...nice man.

08:51.865 --> 08:53.439
You very nice man.

08:53.441 --> 08:56.109
Mommy, you're not gonna
take that, are you?

08:56.111 --> 08:58.519
I am. I am gonna bend over
and I am gonna take it,

08:58.521 --> 09:01.097
because that's what we do
when people upset us.

09:01.099 --> 09:03.099
Mother...

09:03.101 --> 09:06.711
of two is what I am.

09:06.713 --> 09:08.713
Okay.

09:08.715 --> 09:11.383
This is so hard.

09:15.797 --> 09:17.130
<i> There you go.</i>
<i> Lunge. Lunge.</i>

09:17.132 --> 09:18.539
<i> That's right.</i>
<i> 90-degree angle!</i>

09:18.541 --> 09:20.392
<i> You guys are doing great.</i>
<i> Sweet, okay.</i>

09:20.394 --> 09:22.635
<i> For this next one,</i>
<i> you can use any household item</i>

09:22.637 --> 09:24.712
<i> if you don't have any weights</i>
<i> at home.</i>

09:24.714 --> 09:26.790
<i> I like to use</i>
<i> a large bottle of shampoo.</i>

09:26.792 --> 09:29.216
<i> We're just gonna do some</i>
<i> tricep extensions.</i>

09:29.218 --> 09:31.236
Oh, you're walking.

09:31.238 --> 09:32.979
And there's color
in your face.

09:32.981 --> 09:35.982
Yeah, I think
the last of it is out.

09:35.984 --> 09:37.801
The tea you made
really helped.

09:37.803 --> 09:40.120
Aww.
Thank you.

09:41.139 --> 09:42.897
I think
it was food poisoning.

09:42.899 --> 09:46.309
I might have eaten some bad
Shrimp Louie yesterday.

09:46.311 --> 09:47.919
Not Petruzzo's.

09:47.921 --> 09:49.254
Petruzzo's.
Oh, my God!

09:49.256 --> 09:51.238
That is so gross!
Dan!

09:51.240 --> 09:53.258
They gave me back my coat
and there was a mouse

09:53.260 --> 09:55.151
eating a tissue
in the pocket!

09:55.153 --> 09:57.095
I have never seen you scream
like that.

09:57.097 --> 09:59.914
Your face was just
an open mouth.

09:59.916 --> 10:01.600
[ Laughs ]

10:01.602 --> 10:02.992
Yeah, just like that.
No!

10:02.994 --> 10:06.253
[ Both laugh ]

10:06.255 --> 10:08.273
I promise,
next anniversary,

10:08.275 --> 10:09.590
I will choose a restaurant

10:09.592 --> 10:12.110
where the rodents stay safely
on the floor.

10:12.112 --> 10:14.762
[ Both laugh ]

10:14.764 --> 10:15.855
[ Snorts ]

10:16.007 --> 10:17.932
Oh, the laughter,
it's j-jostling the, uh...

10:17.934 --> 10:19.767
[ Gurgling ]
...warm shrimp.

10:19.769 --> 10:21.678
[ Laughing ]
Good luck up there.

10:21.680 --> 10:24.581
[ Laughs ]

10:26.034 --> 10:32.464
♪♪

10:32.466 --> 10:33.632
[ Cellphone chimes ]

10:33.634 --> 10:35.425
[ Chuckles ]

10:40.866 --> 10:46.627
♪♪

10:46.629 --> 10:52.208
♪♪

10:52.210 --> 10:53.485
She originally started
dating you

10:53.487 --> 10:56.229
because of
the free frozen yogurt.

10:56.231 --> 10:59.807
But then she fell madly in love
with me?

10:59.809 --> 11:02.068
Deeply, deeply, madly.

11:02.070 --> 11:04.737
You were all
she talked about.

11:04.739 --> 11:05.830
And I'm done.

11:05.832 --> 11:08.391
Mm.
Try to get out of
that one.

11:08.393 --> 11:10.393
Yeah, okay.

11:10.395 --> 11:11.728
Oh.

11:11.730 --> 11:12.820
Oh.

11:12.822 --> 11:13.988
Wow.

11:13.990 --> 11:15.156
You're really good
at this.

11:15.158 --> 11:16.591
You should get into
kidnapping.

11:18.253 --> 11:20.737
So, tell me something
she said about me.

11:20.739 --> 11:24.498
I mean, she was just
really proud of you.

11:24.500 --> 11:28.428
You had such an important job,
saving people.

11:28.430 --> 11:33.082
Touching all those gross
body parts, all those fluids.

11:33.084 --> 11:34.267
That's it?

11:34.269 --> 11:37.011
Well, she thought you looked
great in scrubs.

11:37.013 --> 11:38.179
[ Chuckles ]

11:38.181 --> 11:40.273
She thought you were
a superhero, you know?

11:40.275 --> 11:42.367
Sarah Man.
[ Laughs ]

11:42.369 --> 11:44.536
She was really proud of you
being a doctor.

11:46.522 --> 11:49.749
Okay, well,
I'm gonna go bag groceries now.

11:52.120 --> 11:53.861
Are you mad?
I'm picking up a tone.

11:53.863 --> 11:56.214
You just told me Coleen
was proud of me because
I was a doctor,

11:56.216 --> 11:58.291
and now I'm not a doctor
anymore,

11:58.293 --> 12:00.367
so my feelings are hurt.

